</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>6.0</li><li>53.1</li><li>36.9</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{10}^{{2}}={8}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{100}={64}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{100}-{64}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{36}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{36}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{10}}\right)}}}\approx{53.130102354156}\approx{53.1}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{10}}\right)}}}\approx{36.869897645844}\approx{36.9}</m></p>

</solution>
